        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 5:48PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 548 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Woodrow, or 25 miles southeast of Fort Morgan, moving northeast at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 50 mph, and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Woodrow.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If a tornado is spotted seek shelter inside a sturdy building.</instruction>
